Contributor Code of Conduct
As contributors and maintainers of this project, we are committed to fostering an open and welcoming environment. We value respect, inclusivity, and cooperation among all participants in the project.

Our Standards
In the interest of promoting a positive experience for everyone, we encourage the following behaviors:

Being Respectful: Show respect for differing viewpoints and experiences. Polite and constructive feedback is encouraged.
Using Inclusive Language: Be welcoming and considerate in your choice of language.
Collaborating Openly: Share knowledge and resources freely, and help others in need.
Acknowledging Contributions: Give credit where itâ€™s due, recognizing the efforts and contributions of others.
Maintaining a Positive Environment: Seek to resolve conflicts constructively.
We also expect everyone to refrain from:

Harassment and Discrimination: Any form of harassment, discriminatory language, or offensive comments based on personal characteristics will not be tolerated.
Disruptive or Dismissive Behavior: This includes trolling, insulting remarks, or deliberately disrupting discussions.
Personal Attacks: Criticize ideas, not people. Avoid negative personal remarks or comments aimed at individuals.
Scope
This Code of Conduct applies to all project spaces, including issues, pull requests, comments, and other forms of communication, whether online or in person.

Enforcement
Instances of unacceptable behavior may be reported to the project maintainer at [fasinfasi17@gmail.com]. All reports will be reviewed and investigated promptly. The project team is committed to maintaining confidentiality and will take appropriate corrective actions if necessary.

Attribution
This Code of Conduct is adapted from the Contributor Covenant, version 2.1.

Feel free to personalize this document, particularly the contact email address, to ensure it reflects your project's specifics and enforcement policies.
